= SDL_GetScancodeName =
Use this function to get a human-readable name for a scancode.


== Syntax ==
```c++
const char* SDL_GetScancodeName(SDL_scancode scancode)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''scancode'''
|the desired [[SDL_scancode]] to query ???
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns a pointer to a UTF-8 string that stays valid at least until the next call to this function. If you need it around any longer, you must copy it. If the scancode doesn't have a name, this function returns an empty string ("").  <<Color2(green,Should scancode here be bold?  Should the pointer be mentioned?)>>

